To assess divided attention (multitasking), we measured the difficulty threshold level reached at each time point for both the perceptual discrimination and visuomotor tracking multitasking modules. To assess sustained attentional control, we averaged RT across both portions of the ACE-X continuous performance task (frequent and infrequent targets). To assess working memory, we averaged the maximum span correctly achieved on the forwards and backwards span tasks. A Greenhouse–Geisser correction was used when appropriate. Effect sizes in ANOVAs are reported as partial eta squared (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
